              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:θεός&lt;SDBG:θεός:000000&gt;}[a] ‘God,’ {D:12.1}) the nature or state of being God</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>deity</Gloss>
                <Gloss>divine nature</Gloss>
                <Gloss>divine being</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The expression ‘divine nature’ may be rendered in a number of languages as ‘just what God is like’ or ‘how God is’ or ‘what God is.’ In {S:04500102000036} ‘deity’ may sometimes be expressed as ‘the fact that he is God’ or ‘… is truly God.’|In {S:06100100400028} ‘to share in the very being of God,’ one may speak of ‘to share in what God is like’ or ‘to become in a measure like God.’ It is important, of course, to avoid the implication that people can become completely God.</Comments>
